Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium light brown. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol.
Type series: KT935 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 10. Names, Hipparchos, Dionysios, Leon.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0335)
